In this statement, the President expresses his sadness over the loss of two miners in Kentucky and extends his thoughts and prayers to their families. He also emphasizes that he refuses to accept miner deaths as the cost of mining and believes it is the responsibility of everyone, including mine operators and the federal government, to prevent such tragedies from occurring. The President mentions that his administration is taking actions to demand accountability for safety violations and strengthen mine safety to ensure the protection of all miners.